caption: Enjoyed th atmosphere and food service was great. Food was good but little over priced for what you got. Bread is bland. Food 7of 10 everything else is great

Overall, very disappointed with both the service we received as well as the quality of food. Finding our server was very difficult and we had to ask for items multiple times before we would receive them. The food was very disappointing in both flavor and quality. The wedge salad was not a wedge but rather, a thin slice from an iceberg head. The dressing was very runny and lacked the strong flavor you should have with a blue cheese. My filet mignon (cooked rare as requested) was sadly not a quality cut of meat. A filet should melt in your mouth, but I found myself struggling to chew it. It also sadly lacked any flavor that you should be getting from a prime cut of filet. The French style mashed potatoes were also a disappointment. French style mashed potatoes are generally a cheesy blend of potatoes with hints of rosemary and garlic. (Aligot) Sadly, these potatoes tasted like a blend of real potatoes and instant mashed potatoes with little to no seasoning. For the price of $260 for two adults, I'm disappointed. I've dined at many exclusive restaurants across the US, especially in Miami, and I'm saddened that this steakhouse fell very short of expectations. $260 should get you an incredible culinary experience; not a bland, disappointing meal.

-STAFF: Super welcoming on arrival. 10/10 -FOOD: Steak frites 10/10, 8oz.filet mignon 10/10 cooked perfectly Mashed potatoes 10/10 super creamy and garlicy Side of broccoli: 8/10 ONLY because I’m not a fan of the sauce, but my guest said 10/10. -ATMOSPHERE: very beautiful and lax inside. The aroma when walking in smelled like fresh bread super nice. The moscato wine was also super delicious. One of the best I’ve had. Overall, I am coming back. I definitely recommend.

We had dinner here for our anniversary. When making the reservation we noted it was our anniversary and requested to be seated in a romantic area. Instead when we arrived, our table was not ready and the hostess/waitress sat us upstairs in what I would consider to be the overflow area. There was no ambiance, the candle on the table wasn’t even lit. I was quite disappointed.  I’ve been to many steakhouses that are always so accommodating for special occasions. Our food was okay but the bedding for the branzino reminded me of rice-a-roni and I was not a fan. The steak and drinks were good. The service was a bit subpar but they did provide complimentary champagne. Based on my overall experience, I’ll likely choose another steakhouse when we dine.
Perfect everytime!  One of the best!

The food is amazing. Got the 6oz Filet Mignon with a side of Brussel sprouts with prosciutto. It was to die for. Especially the Brussel sprouts. The butter sauce that it was laid one top of.. ooo flame 🤤

I am very upset with the experience we had at GT prime from the staff to the food. We had a reservation for 830pm on 2/13.  First of all, we were told that we would only have 1.5 hrs to dine when we were seated. However, when I booked on open table, it clearly said up to 1 hr and 45 minutes for parties up to 6. After 1.5 hrs from being there, we were told our time was up and we had to leave. I literally had to chug my wine so we could leave! We had just spent $300 for dinner, and I couldn’t even enjoy my wine.I understand, we are in a middle of a pandemic, but don’t advertise a different time limit when making a reservation online. Also, if you are going to enforce the time limit, be fair and do it for all your guests. There were several other couples that we there before us and were still there when we left.  Second of all, our waiter barely checked in on us. He would walk by and not even ask how things were.  Third, I asked for my steak to be cooked medium.It was brought to me black and blue. I had to flagged our waiter to tell  him it needed to be cooked more. This took more time from our 1.5 hr table time limit. It was brought back to me, but this time rare. They still couldn’t get the temperature right. The steaks were also extremely salty. We were not compensated for this bad food experience, but instead, were kicked out after 1.5 hrs. Unbelievable!  I have been to many many different steakhouses in the city, and GT prime is by far the worst one! Bad staff and food. Save yourself some money and do not go. You will regret it.

Drove through the February snow storm and I just want to give Brian and Tommy the biggest thank you I can. I fell in the ice after parking, Brian immediately offered me ice and kept checking on me. Then Tommy was so on point as a server. Thanks guys. You made the night way better. Thank you. -Tay

Probably the best level of service I’ve had at a Chicago Steakhouse...and that’s a high standard. Attentive and well-paced. Price point is fair for quality of product. Our steaks were cooked as ordered and excellent pieces of meat. We added a couple of sides and they were....ok.....but not enough to detract from what was an outstanding dinner.

GT Prime competes with the other high-end Chicago steakhouses, so I grade it on the same curve. Our party of four visited on a Saturday night in early December and had a very enjoyable meal. The main dining room is essentially all booths with a couple chairs, which is nice for those with different preferences. The environment is typically steakhouse-dark, but with a modern touch. Service was wonderful -- friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable. The bussers were on top of their game, at our service almost before we recognized the need.
A favorite.
Food was so delish. The staff was friendly and observant. The place has a good atmosphere.
Cute small nook. Not impressed with the food. Lots of ambience and cool cocktails. Mediocre customer service. Staffing on the cell phones texting behind the stations.

The octopus with zucchini purée was great! My wife did the risotto, which she thought was perfect. I did the Snake River Farms American Strip ‘Wagyu’...which was highly recommended by our awesome waiter Ben. It was by far one of the best steaks I’ve ever had! Desert was the apple pie which was also great. GT PRIME is a definite must to check out! Thanks Ben for the great recommendations and service!!

Food was solid, steakhouse, cooked right. Room is an interesting spin on the dark wood steakhouse standard. So everything was right, but it is always just going to be a steakhouse.

Everything we had was great - cocktails, appetizers, entrees and deserts. The service was a great balance of attentive and helpful, but not nagging. And without exaggeration, the filet was the best I have ever had in my life - I even had a dream about eating it again two days later.
Honestly, thinking back on the great places to eat and my experience here comparatively... This place is kind of underwhelming for its price point. Unfortunate.

Do you want to impress a colleague, boss or date? Take them to GT Prime! The ambiance is gorgeous and the service is impeccable. The Chef was so gracious and could not be any nicer. You can tell he really stands behind his food. Amazing!

The others in our group had a prime ny strip and it was not over salted. Wife had the fish and gnocchi the fish is fine the gnocchi was horrible. We came here for NYE dinner. Our res was for 7:30 however our table was not ready so we sat at the bar and had a drink while we waited. Around 8:00, our table was ready. It seemed like there were several empty tables so idk why there was a wait. They led us to the very awkward upstairs section of the restaurant, where there is bad LED lighting and only 4 tables. I requested that we move downstairs which they accommodated immediately. We're pretty young so maybe we were being judged for dining at a nice restaurant, which is why they put us upstairs. We ended up in an awesome booth in the corner of the main dining room, probably one of the best seats in the house. We ordered the lump crab and avocado app which was delish and super fresh. We ordered a bottle of decent red wine, the Chicago Style ribeye, a filet mignon, mashed potatoes and brussels. Our food was fab, steaks were cooked to perfection which is obviously our #1 biggest concern when dining at a steakhouse. My only true complaint is that we felt very rushed throughout our dinner. Maybe because it was NYE, but after sitting down at our table late, ordering, and eating, we were done within an hour. We kept asking if we could take our time to order as well but the waiter insisted that the food would take a while so we could take our time. Sure enough, it was out 10 minutes later. I'd probably return on a night that isn't going to be so busy to give them another chance.

Wouldnt really go there ever again. My first steak dinner in Chicago came with this oily and salty meal. The filet mignon was too dark outside like it was grilled for too long and the food isn’t hot either. The scallops was pretty salty, again. So do the risotto in the picture. I would say the quality of service is the only outstanding thing here but food, wouldn’t ever come back considering the price.

Everything is delicious and well presented.  Thank you from our family for a memorable evening on Sunday August 18th, 2019.  We shall return!!!   Mark Masi and family.

Overall, I was tremendously disappointed with our GT Prime experience.  The food was not bad, but literally every part of the experience was lacking.  I would not recommend this to anyone, for more details read on. Service/Food: Everyone in our section ended up getting the wrong orders at least once.  the table next to us got the wrong order twice.  We also got food so fast that we never got a chance to enjoy our cocktails, despite talking to the server (based on the advice of the table next to us) about wanting to slow our meal down and enjoy our courses.  We ended up with plates arriving on top of other plates.  When they brought me the wrong cut of meat and I sent it back the correct cut of meat wasn't cooked properly.  I just ate it because at this point I didn't want to deal with it anymore.  We didn't get any of the sauces that we ordered until we asked a second time for them, and the server never apologized or addressed it in anyway.  In fact, once our food showed our server pretty much disappeared.  The cooking of the steaks showed a lack of interest or knowledge in that they were either over cooked or dramatically under cooked, or actually the wrong cut.  The french fries were soggy.  The foie gras was lovely. The tomato salad was OK. Seating: We were seated in a VERY intimate table where one of us was on a shared bench and the other was on a nice seat.  This is normally fine except in this case the shared bench was worn and extra soft causing the person on the bench to be approximately 6 inches lower than the person in the chair.  It made it hard to eat at the table.  In addition the tables were so small and close together that we were basically eating with the two tables next to us.  We decided to not order anything for after dinner because our experience was so bad.
Delicious food. Amazing interior design. Good staff.
Excellent food and atmosphere. If you go to Chicago this spot is a must. All our dishes were prepared to perfection and we had a party of 6

I walked into GT Prime & smelled the intoxicating aromas in the air & told my wife, "I'm home." and immediately knew that we would be back. We went to celebrate a friend's birthday  and it was an amazing experience for all 22 of us. Everyone in our party really enjoyed all of the dishes, that we shared as a group, ranging from the 3 Seafood Towers, to all of the shareable sides (mashed potatoes, asparagus, broccoli, & succulent mushrooms). The entrees ranged from salmon, to ribeye, to bison tenderloin, to wagyu, and all proved to exceed expectations & caused me to (selfishly) plot when to come back to try each & every entree myself. The bar service was outstanding, and the libations produced at the bar were all  amazing and consistent. The servers did an exceptional job juggling our drink orders, food orders, birthday speeches, & more drink orders, & more food orders. The service that we received was truly top notch & I am grateful that we all had such a memorable experience for our great friend's birthday. We will definitely be back!

(Translated by Google) Quality and very good treatment. The place cozy while modern. Good choice for meals as a couple or company.  (Original) Calidad y muy buen trato. El sitio acogedor a la vez que moderno. Buena elección para comidas en pareja o de empresa.

Upscale steakhouse serving a wonderful menu of primarily steak and seafood. Price point was fair and service matched cost. Cozy environment with dimmed lights, booths, fur covered chairs, and more. Great experience with the staff and the food was delightful. The menu has options for everyone, and great shareable sides and starters for larger groups as well as smaller groups. I would recommend checking this place out.

I was a little disappointed when our waiter told us that they weren't serving dry-aged steaks on the night we went, but surprisingly the Kansas City strip steak (which our waiter recommended) was one of the best steaks I've had in a long time. Great service and friendly staff!

Four of us dined here for a birthday dinner. The atmosphere was wonderful and the service was good. The food portions we're huge and we ended up taking a lot of food home. Overall a good restaurant for any special occasion.
Food was delicious! Really amazing steak. Service was really rushed though. Felt like they really wanted us out of there ...

Been here a few times now, each time with great service and especially great steaks. Drinks have always been good as well, but try and make a reservation and dress a little better than casually. It's a wonderful environment but big groups and families sometime interfere with the atmosphere.
A great Chicago steakhouse with an awesome wine list.
Great place for a birthday dinner! One of the best steak places in town.
great ambience, service and food.  quality of meat, seasoning and portion is outstanding
Hands down one of my favorite restaurants in the city.

Great atmosphere. Good steak, not Great.

My wife and I love GT Prime for special occasions or simply as a Sunday evening spot to have a nice dinner together. Very professional staff and beautiful decor.
Fantastic meal and service, very happy with everything I was served. Prices are decent as well!
Good steaks, but a horrible management and complete chaos in their procedures.
Had a wonderful Birthday date. Definitely coming back!
The food is great. Really delicious.  The service is superb but the prices are very high

Went to GT Prime for Chicago Restaurant Week 2019. The atmosphere is amazing, I love the decor and the cozy ambiance of the restaurant. For the prices, I would have expected slightly better food. The appetizers were good, but the entrees were nothing special for the price. Someone in our party ordered off the regular menu (not restaurant week) and the steak was incredibly tough and fatty. The restaurant did offer him a new meal, but I wouldn’t have expected that experience for a $50-60 steak. Overall fun dinner spot, but I think there are better places for the price/food. The drinks were good, so may be a better cocktail/appetizer spot.
Bustling steakhouse.  Awesome food and drink , awesome wait  staff.
Very sexy chic steakhouse. Love coming here. Atmosphere is top notch,  somewhere to impress someone
Pricey but worth it. Great wine list.

Disappointed that a restaurant with such high prices can deliver a less than stellar meal.    My salad  included pork belly that was way over cooked and tough.  My wife’s bone-in filet, ordered “rare plus” was delivered well done.  They graciously took it back and the new filet, although done to her liking, was tough.  The other diners at our table were satisfied but all felt the filets were lacking in flavor.  Service was exceptional but there are better steakhouses elsewhere.
Service was excellent! I had the bison steak which was amazing. Brussel sprouts were great too.

One of the best steakhouses I’ve visited. I got the wagyu steak- it was better than I expected. The service was great, the drinks are highly crafted and made to perfection. They serve super fresh seafood here from their other restaurant, GT Seafood. If you have never tried wagyu beef, this is the place for it! I highly recommend reservations for The weekend. Expect to be wowed!

The team at GT Prime are in a class of their own. Food is always on point, service is phenomenal, Mike D is a human encyclopedia of perfectly cooked meats and seafood. The steak (porterhouse) was cooked perfectly and definitely get the Mac and cheese and Brussels sprouts. You will not regret it.

The bone marrow was mouth watering and the Wagyu steak was melt in your mouth. Enjoyed the array of salts provided and the drink menu. Slightly disappointed in the size of the scallop entree, but not enough to lower the rating. We celebrated our engagement here, and the staff helped us make it a night to remember!

Always super tasty, easily our favorite steak house in the city. They had an amazing prime rib on special, definitely grab it if it’s still on the menu. Otherwise, Kansas strip is always fantastic, as are the shishito peppers and scallops!
Great meal, nice place.
Fantastic steaks, and food in general!  The bison is incredible.  The waygu is always phenomenal as well

My all time favorite restaurant in Chicago right now.  The food is spectacular,  the service is impeccable. The drinks are top notch.  Prime Rib is on special right now and it is the absolute best I've ever had.

Great steaks they accidentally messed up my order and gave me a ribeye instead of a KC strip which I ordered. They went above and beyond to make it right...nevertheless both cuts were awesome. I look forward to coming back. Also very good Moscow Mule.
Phenomenal service and delicious food. Not much else to say.
(Translated by Google) Excellent. Atmosphere, choice of wines. Delicious food  (Original) Excellent. Ambiance, choix de vins. Mets délicieux

Great menu with execution and service perfect. I had lamb and the four chops were meaty, tender and cooked to a perfect medium rare. The octopus appetizer was to die for, kind of octopus Mac and cheese and the truffle pasta was heavenly too. Absolutely nothing to be critical of and all was noteworthy. Definitely a repeater.
Great service. Had an issue with my steak, server immediately noticed had corrected the problem.
Terrific! Will certainly be actually returning once again. The site is actually excellent for me.

Bit pricey but really good meats. Avoid the wagyu which will be disappointing if you are familiar with wagyu. Also the lesser priced venison is super tender and the bison is incredibly full of flavour. Also some really good wines.
It was alright.  Mashed potatoes were incredible.  Steak was good but less that what I would have expected.
Fantastic service and food. I would highly recommend trying GT Prime. The bone in filet and bone marrow appetizer were delicious!

Excellent way to spend our anniversary. The food was prepared to perfection and the staff left nothing to be desired. The dry aged ribeye was very flavorful and the cocktails were mixed and presented with care. Our server Matt took exceptional care of us and we will be back!

One of the excellent "New" steakhouses in Chicago, where the entire menu is amazing, in addition to steaks.  My wife and I decided to share a salad, 2 appetizers, a steak and a dessert - ended up with an excellent 5 course meal.  The bone marrow is a nice twist on this popular ingredient - where many restaurants serve it but provide just a tiny portion for the price.  GT Prime added cheese and other elements to "buff" up into a very sharable dish.  We also had the 45-day aged bone-in ribeye - another great dish for two!
Our group of four shared the carnivore and we were not disappointed. Highly recommend.

Steaks are Excellent Vegetable quality poor Asparagus was to mature and tough...plus over stated in simple steamed and garnished with nuts would be prefered. Service is Good...except one Starter never came out Ambience and seating is very nice Would return again
Great food . Loved the place My now favourite in Chicago
Great place for special occasion. They really pamper you. Great food and superb service!

GT Prime lived up to the hype I received from chefs in Kansas City.  Andrea did an excellent job explaining the menu, kept the table nice and tidy, and her choices for sides, the corn and the brussel sprouts were outstanding.  My Dad and I already had the steaks we want picked out before hand.  45 day dry age was very tasty. Love that funk and can't get enough. Filet with truffles was extremely tender.  The A5 wagyu is a game changer and instantly makes any restaurant a destination option.  Worth every penny, savor each bite. The tender richness of A5 cannot be surpassed.  Thank you for letting my Dad and I dine with Lou Brock and we'll be sure to tell others and we will be back when we make it back to Chicago.  The service here is outstanding. Food is great. Well priced. Start with the bone marrow.
This place is EXQUISITE in every way!!! Very BEAUTIFUL and romantic with succulent flavors in every dish!!
Excellent food with service to match!

Celebrated a birthday of a friend here. Very nice interior. Pleasant staff and service. Food is as follows to my taste:  1- first time disappointed with an aged bone-in ribeye. Don't get the dry aged 45 days prime ribeye. It's $98. not worth it. Was not that tender and just not right. I never had a bad ribeye (more then $30) at a steakhouse.  2- don't get the rabbit dish. our waiter/waitress both pushed for it. it was weird tasting.  3- steal tartare and chips were good. but not wow.  4- mashed potato was so so so creamy mostly butter  5- asparagus was classic and good.  6- bone-in filet mignon was the best I ever had! two friends ordered them and they were incredibly flavorful and tender. I really wished I ordered it or if I could return the ribeye and get this first..  7- crab legs are just ok..small portion.  8- chocolate layer cake was OK. strawberry dessert was good.  This steakhouse has no complementary bread.  Briefly, I would come back for the bone-in filet mignon. Don't get the dry aged ribeye here. It's very overpriced. Maybe the regular ribeye here would taste better.
Awesome food and Johnny was great. Would definitely recommend, the shisito corn and mash potatoes were amazing... The filet mignon was delicious.

Excellent dining experience. Husband and I went here last night to celebrate my birthday. Food was very good and the service excellent as well. Our servers name was Darien. She was an awesome server attentive but not intrusive. Although this place is higher end dining it's not pretentious. Its chic and modern. Nice change from the old school type steakhouse. Now the food. It was very good. We had the seafood ceviche and jumbo shrimp as starters. Both were good. I then ordered the Japanese a5 filet, my husband ordered Kansas city strip. Steaks were great.  A5 was melt in your mouth as it should be. I have eaten A5 before and this was a very good cut compared to the rest. GT Prime, Highly recommended by a local, I had the pleasure of their company while dining at this Wells street eatery last evening. We arrived on time and our reservation was in tact as ordered. We were greeted by very friendly Valets who quickly opened both cab and front doors as they welcomed us to GT. The floor manger and two hostess were friendly, addressed our host by her name, and we were escorted to our table . The restaurant is very appropriately decorated and comfortably furnished. I mention this as so many Chicago up scale eateries have arranged the tables so close that one has difficulty getting in and out and private conversations don't exist. Service was on spot from delivery of the wine list, menus and a brief but accurate description of featured items. A bottle of "Chateau Durfort - Vivens, Margaux 2006" was selected, properly presented, chilled and décantered. The General Manager stopped by briefly to welcome us and offer any questions or explanations needed and exchanged cards. A sampling of appetizers, entrées and desserts got the three of us gave a varied and filling of GT's bill of fare and the ability and skills of their culinary team. A "high five" to the kitchen crew!! Throughout the evening staff and service was friendly and impeccable. Five stars to GT Prime  Rick Price, FMP "2006 Kentucky Restaurateur of The Year"

Chef Giuseppe Tentori gets 5 stars for this restaurant where your experience will exceed your expectations. Chicago has no shortage of ordinary steakhouses, but GT Prime is simply outstanding for small plate concept. The food is unbelievable from appetizers to desert!!!! The service is perfect!!(Alex our waitress). You can share small plates of different steaks that are truly delicious. The wine selection is impressive. Our party of 8 at Chef's table placed this place on the top 5 of their favorite. From the front of the  restaurant to kitchen this place is extraordinary.

GT Prime has excellent food and cocktails, but you will pay a premium price for it. It's tough to get a reservation here so book very far in advance! I've been here twice, the first time the group I was with got a mixture of different cuts of meat - 5 pieces of 4 different types. They were all really well cooked, but they are pretty bite sized, so we supplemented with sides. The crafted cocktails are excellent, I had both the smoking gun and the x-ray yankee zulu, suited well for fans of whiskey forward cocktails. The second time I came back I didn't feel it was worth spending the price of the cuts again so I got the burger, which was cooked very well to my liking (medium rare) and tasted great. All in all this place is worth the experience for a special occasion, but given how hard it is to get a table here and the high menu prices, it's probably not going to be a regular dinner place for most people.
